description: TEHRAN- Lebanon’s Hezbollah resistance movement has unleashed a barrage of missiles and artillery fire at Israeli military sites in response to the regime’s attacks against the Mediterranean country.
title: Military adventurism spells doom for Israel

description: TEHRAN- The armed forces of the Ansarullah government in Yemen's capital Sana'a have claimed responsibility for a drone attack that struck a sensitive area in central Tel Aviv close to the U.S. embassy.
title: Ansarullah a thorn in the side of Israel

description: TEHRAN – A tragic terrorist attack in Saravan, located in Iran's southeastern province of Sistan and Baluchestan, has resulted in the death of a police officer.
title: Iranian police officer killed in southeastern province terrorist attack

description: TEHRAN – On Friday, Nasser Kanaani, spokesperson for Iran's Foreign Ministry, sharply criticized a recent resolution passed by the Israeli parliament (Knesset) that rejects the establishment of a Palestinian state.
title: Tehran criticizes Knesset move as evidence of Israeli’s ‘racist’ policies

description: TEHRAN – The spokesperson for the National Security and Foreign Policy Committee of Iranian parliament has emphasized that Iran's approach to the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) adheres to the safeguards and regulations outlined in the Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT).
title: Iran acts according to safeguards, NPT: AEOI chief

description: TEHRAN- The first supervisory session of the National Security Committee of the Parliament was held on Thursday with the participation of deputy speaker of Parliament for laws and representatives from the ministries of Intelligence and Defense.
title: Parliamentary Committee holds first supervisory session with ministry officials

description: TEHRAN- Iranian Ambassador to Russia Kazem Jalali has met with Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Mikhail Galuzin to discuss issues related to the situation in the South Caucasus region.
title: Iran envoy meets Russian deputy FM

description: TEHRAN- The president of Guinea Conakry and Hungary’s president extended congratulations to Masoud Pezeshkian on his election as the president of the Islamic Republic of Iran.
title: Foreign leaders Congratulates Pezeshkian on election as Iran's new president

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian envoy to Armenia spoke on the territorial disputes between Yerevan and Baku, saying Iran respects international law and opposes any unlawful geopolitical changes in the region.
title: Tehran reiterates firm opposition to geopolitical changes in South Caucasus

description: TEHRAN- A member of the presiding board of the Islamic Consultative Assembly has announced that the members of the Parliament will meet the Leader of the Islamic Revolution on Sunday 21st July.
title: Lawmakers to meet with Leader: Official

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Navy hosts the Joint Caspian Sea Search and Rescue Exercise, "CASAREX24," from July 19 to July 21.
title: Iran hosts joint Caspian Sea search and rescue exercise

description: TEHRAN – Iran's acting Foreign Minister, Ali Baqeri Kani, announced that the country will utilize all available domestic and international legal avenues to ensure those responsible for the assassination of its top anti-terror commander, Lieutenant General Qassem Soleimani, are brought to justice.
title: Tehran pledges legal efforts to bring perpetrators of Gen. Soleimani's assassination to justice

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Kayhan addressed the claim of a Western-oriented website.
title: The dream of negotiating with the future president of America!

description: U.S. House Speaker Mike Johnson has said some Democratic lawmakers may try to interrupt Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s address to a joint session of Congress next week but that they will be arrested if need be, the Times of Israel reported.
title: House speaker: Disruption of Netanyahu speech could lead to arrest

description: A top United Nations human rights expert has called for Israel to lose its seat on the international body over a “criminal attack” on the institution’s Palestinian base, according to the Independent.
title: Albanese: Unseat Israel from UN

description: Food shortages are continuing to plague Palestinians in northern Gaza, many of whom depend on charity groups to get just one meal a day.
title: Northern Gaza residents ‘resort to eating grass’

description: Protesting students have returned to the streets of the Bangladeshi capital Dhaka, defying a ban on public rallies following a day of clashes which left dozens dead.
title: Bangladesh students defy ban to continue protests

description: Palestinian fighters with the National Resistance Brigades reported destroying an Israeli armored personnel carrier using an improvised explosive device (IED) in Rafah city’s Kaf al-Mashrou area on Thursday, war monitors reported.
title: National Resistance Brigades: Israeli armored vehicle destroyed in Rafah

description: The 60-bed Red Cross field hospital in Rafah, southern Gaza, is nearly at full capacity following repeated mass casualty events. They include the attack in Al-Mawasi on Saturday that sent 26 injured patients into the facility for treatment, including children suffering from shrapnel wounds. It is the latest in a series of mass casualty events that Red Cross workers have responded to since May.
title: ICRC: Medical needs in Gaza dramatically outstrip limited healthcare response

description: The International Court of Justice said on Friday it can give a non-binding advisory opinion on Israel's “occupation” of Palestinian territories, rejecting calls by Israel and a handful of other countries to refuse to give one.
title: ICJ: Settlements in West Bank illegal

description:
* Paintings by MAD are being shown in an exhibition now underway at E1 Gallery. 
The exhibit named “The World Next Door” will run until August 2 at the gallery located at 1 Hamid Dead End, off Lesani Alley, Jebheh St., off Mahdieh St. in the Elahieh neighborhood.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian film “The Old Bachelor” written and directed by Oktay Baraheni won an award at the 36th Galway Film Fleadh in Ireland, which was held from July 9 to 14.
title: Oktay Baraheni’s “The Old Bachelor” wins at Ireland’s Galway Film Fleadh

description: TEHRAN- The cinematheque of the Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art is set to screen Jordanian film director and writer Darin J. Sallam’s 2021 film “Farha” on Sunday, coinciding with the ongoing "A Carving on Stone" art exhibition.
title: Tehran museum to screen “Farha” on Palestinian cause

description: TEHRAN-Iranian painter Farhad Moshiri passed away on Wednesday in Tehran due to cardiac arrest. He was 61, IRNA reported.
title: Iranian painter Farhad Moshiri passes away at 61

description: A widespread Microsoft outage linked to cybersecurity firm Crowdstrike disrupted flights, banks, media outlets and companies around the world on Friday and highlighted dependence on software from a handful of providers.
title: Global cyber outage disrupts media, grounds flights

description: TEHRAN – Gilan province, one of the most sought-after travel destinations in Iran, has recorded some 26 million overnight stays throughout the first quarter of current Persian year (started on March 20), a local official announced.
title: Gilan records 26 million overnight stays in Q1

description: TEHRAN – A number of traditional houses, suitable for conversion into eco-lodges have been singled out across the county, said a local official in charge of cultural heritage.
title: Potential houses to become eco-lodges in Ramsar

description: TEHRAN - To enhance the accessibility of local handicrafts to tourists, Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari’s handicrafts department has launched some new markets and centers this summer, according to a local official.
title: Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari expands craft markets for tourism’s sake

description: TEHRAN - Nestled deep within the rugged Zagros Mountains, the mausoleum of Imamzadeh Bibi Hakimeh, attracts domestic visitors and pilgrims from countries like Kuwait, Bahrain, the UAE, Qatar, Lebanon, Iraq, Saudi Arabia, and Syria.
title: Discover spiritual serenity of Bibi Hakimeh mausoleum

description: TEHRAN - A total of 482 foreign travelers attended Muharram's mourning rituals in their visits to Yazd province during the first ten days of the lunar month, which ended on the day of Ashura (July 16).
title: 482 foreign travelers attend Muharram rituals in Yazd province

description: XINING- In the second week of July, a team of seven journalists from various esteemed Iranian news agencies visited Xining city in Qinghai province, China.
title: Itinerary to cheerful China

description: TEHRAN – The second delegation of Iranian athletes departed for France on Thursday (July 19) to participate in the 33rd Olympic Games, Paris 2024.
title: Paris 2024: Iran's delegation departs

description: TEHRAN –Observed annually on July 20, World Chess Day highlights chess as an intellectual global game that promotes peace, sustainable development, and education.
title: Chess promotes peace, sustainable development

description: TEHRAN- As announced by the director general of the Iranian Ministry of Agriculture’s Office of Quality Improvement, Processing, and Aquatic Market, the country exported 3,094 tons of trout valued at $6.6 million during the first quarter of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-June 20).
title: Iran exports over 3,000 tons of trout in a quarter

description: TEHRAN –The Geological Survey and Mineral Exploration of Iran (GSI) participated in the BRICS roundtable on geology which was held in Moscow, Russia, from July 15 to 17.
title: Iran attends BRICS roundtable on geology

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Red Crescent Society and Qatar Red Crescent Society have explored the potential to develop bilateral cooperation.
title: IRCS, QRCS discuss ways to enhance co-op

description: TEHRAN –The World Food Program (WFP) has released a report, expounding on activities in Iran over the month of June.
title: WFP releases June report on Iran

description: TEHRAN - The director of Iranian Agriculture Ministry’s wheat and rice project has said the country’s farmers have cultivated rice in 650,000 hectares of land in 19 different provinces across the country.
title: Rice cultivation in Iran expands to 650,000 hectares

description: TEHRAN - Head of Iran's Power Generation, Distribution, and Transmission Company (known as Tavanir) Mostafa Rajabi Mashhadi has said the company has implemented 61 transmission and super distribution network development projects since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20).
title: Tavanir implements 61 power grid development projects

description: TEHRAN - The minister in charge of trade of the Eurasian Economic Commission (EEC) has said the commission is going to consider Iran’s observer status during the next meeting of the union which is due to be held in Armenian capital Yerevan in late September.
title: ‘EAEU to consider Iran’s observer status in next meeting’

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Energy Ministry's spokesman for the electricity sector Mostafa Rajabi Mashhadi has said three new power plant units are going to go on stream by the end of the current Iranian calendar year’s summer (September 22).
title: 3 new power plant units to come on stream by late September

description: To the untrained eye, China’s policy lexicon and political session read-outs often seem vague. However, the Third Plenum of the 20th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China is anything but. The four-day meetings in Beijing revealed a wide range of policies with implications far beyond China’s borders.
title: The Third Plenum: Charting China's Economic Roadmap and Its Global Implications

description: TEHRAN –Persepolis football club completed the signing of Gil Vicente striker Ali Alipour on Thursday.
title: Persepolis complete signing of Ali Alipour

description: TEHRAN - Iranian club Bam Khatoon were drawn alongside Kitchee SC from Hong Kong, and Bhutan’s Royal Thimphu College in Group B of the preliminary stage of the 2024/25 AFC Women's Champions League.
title: Bam Khatoon learn fate at 2024/25 AFC Women's Champions League

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Paracanoe athlete Shahla Behrouzi Rad is optimistic about her performance in the 2024 Paralympic Games.
title: Paracanoer Behrouzi Rad optimistic about Paris 2024
